data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":292,"item_id":"msg_015e3950922fb1990069373d6472b88190991cfaca91ad7568","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"The **Contoso Electronics Whistleblower Policy** is designed to provide a safe and transparent work environment for employees, contractors, and third parties. Below are its key details:\n\n1. **Purpose and Scope**: Encourages individuals to report unethical or illegal activities observed during their tenure at Contoso Electronics.\n\n2. **Definition**: A whistleblower refers to any person who reports illegal, unethical, or contrary-to-policy activities.\n\n3. **Reporting Procedures**:\n   - Contact the Human Resources Department.\n   - Email the Compliance Officer at **compliance@contoso.com**.\n   - Call the Compliance Hotline at **1-800-555-1212**.\n   - Reports can also be made anonymously via the Compliance Hotline.\n\n4. **Details to Provide**:\n   - Time and date of the incident.\n   - Individuals involved.\n   - Description of events.\n   - Evidence related to the incident, if available.\n\n5. **Retaliation Prohibited**: Strict prohibition of any retaliation against whistleblowers, with consequences such as disciplinary action or termination.\n\n6. **Confidentiality**: Whistleblowers’ identities will be kept confidential as much as the law permits.\n\n7. **Investigation**: All reported incidents will be investigated promptly and thoroughly.\n\nThis policy highlights Contoso's commitment to ethical and responsible behavior, ensuring employee safety and promoting accountability throughout the organization.","logprobs":[]}

